			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been thinking lately about how much of a buncha HP whores we all are.  Hps hps hps.  Everyone wants more hps.  When I started playing back in the day (kunark release) I wanted two things: int, and mana.  How about this idea:  Make pet hitpoints scale with player mana pool.  Whenever you summon your pet, it checks your current mana pool, and mulitplies it by 1.2, and then assigns that number for your pet's HPs.  The muliplier would be pet-type dependant, the 1.2 would be earth, 1 for air, and .5 for fire/water.  So a really gimp mage with very basic gear at 65 would have say, 4000 mana.   So that would be a 4800hp earth pet, 4000hp air, and 2000 for fire/water.  Hey...thats like, what we have now!  But, make focus items add to the muliplier.  Say, DPoC adds .1 to all of them.  So now your earth pet is at 5200, and air at 4400.  Gee...sure looks similar to what we have now!  Have GoDS add .13, time focus add .2, and LDoN-raid focus add .22
<br />

<br />
According to EQrankings.com, the best magician in the game has about 7700 mana.  So thats a 11k earth pet, 9.3k air, and 5.5k fire/water.  Those numbers seem extreme of course, but remeber that is THE MOST UBER magician in the game, with LDoN-raid focus!!  Most magicians will be stuck with something much more similar to what we have now.  I certainly think that the BEST magician in the game should have an earth pet which has double the hps over the ultra-casual gimp mage.  The numbers I used here for multipliers are NOT just hypothetical...I think these ARE viable numbers and would work well to make pets scale by gear.  And instead of everyone being hp whores, mana will become valuble again!  I don't know of ANYONE who's bought a 40 mana aug from LDoN...with changes like this I might go for it though!  With a pet like this we COULD be a viable short-term offtank in GoD, which is targeted for players with gear like this.
<br />

<br />
Now, this still doesn't solve the problem of pet damage output.  For pet damage, make it a certain percentage of our mana, and have it scale similar to hit points.  Some numbers I think would be reasonable:  Standard, unfocused earth pet hits for 2% of magicians mana.  Air pet hits for 2.1%, water pet hits for 2.2%, and fire hits for 1%.  So, with your average casual 4000 mana magician thats 80 for earth pet, 84 for air, and 88 for water.  Water pet would backstab for 6% of players mana, so in this case 240.  Have DPoC focus add .1% damage, GoDS .2%, Time focus .3%, and LDoN-raid focus .4%.  So with DPoC, earth hits for 90, air  hits for 94, and water hits 98 backstabbing for 250.  
<br />

<br />
Again, the MOST UBER magician according to eqrankings.com is at ~7700 mana.  So, assuming he has LDoN-raid focus, his earth pet would hit for 184, air for 192, water for 200 backstabbing at 492.  Damn, thats uber isn't it?  Check out his magelo: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490514" target="_blank">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490514</a>  Type 8 (Time+) gear in EVERY slot, except for one earring is the Fennin Ro one, every piece augmented with something good, 693 AAs.  There aren't many mages like this folks...hell, the top mage on RN is 500 mana (or 700 pet hps / 12 max hit on earth pet) behind him.  
<br />

<br />
I think these changes are VERY reasonable, and would help us scale MUCH better with our equipment.  It even makes sense from a RP perspective, if you think about it.  We're casters, our power is in our mana (or should be anyways), and the pet would reflect this power.  This would put us back at the top in the damage department at the high end game, and I feel would make magicians a MUCH more desireable class to play.  It would allow me to look forward to improving my character much more, because at the moment I realize the power gain I recieve from time level gear isn't even close to that of the melees, who will all soon overshadow me in damage, which is all I do (I'm in an Ele guild close to achieving time acess, my gear is not uber).  Note that these changes would only affect magician (and perhaps beastlord) pets, and only our 61-65 pets and MS4 (which would have its base damage mod made equal to our air pet, and prism skin would in turn be cast more frequently and absorb 2 hits, to make it better fit the role as a raid pet).  The epic pet does not require this scaling, as it is not intended to scale with the planes of power expansion and beyond.
<br />

<br />
Phew, I think I got it all in there, most of the math is rounded for simplicity.  What do you think guys?  I believe this is THE answer.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370607" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tiiden Vandorgriffin</a>
<br />
65 Magician, Rodcet Nife</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Tiiden Vandorgriffin on Sun Apr 11, 2004 10:53 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
