				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I take exception to the word "gimp" even though I don't fall into that category.  
<br />

<br />
So let me see if I understand your proposition correctly.  You want the top end average player to not only have:
<br />

<br />
1. 3000 more HP
<br />
2. 3000 more mana
<br />
3. Double or triple the FT
<br />
4. Triple the resists
<br />
5. Exp areas twice as good (yeah I love PoE and PoF and when you go back to BoT or even tactics you notice like it like a flash of light in your eyes)
<br />

<br />
As the average player but you want his pet to do anywhere from 50-100% more damage?  Briliiant!!  Create more desparity!
<br />

<br />
By your system, since by default the high end player moves through content atleast twice as fast as the normal person, the disparity will widen, creating a greater rift a year down the road.
<br />

<br />
No your suggestion only helps the upper tiers, not the player base so it is faulty.  And yes EVERYONE should be upgraded.  I'm tired of hearing "What do they need to have a better pet, better nukes... if they aren't doing the harder content."  I remember back in the day when pets summoned at random level and I petitioned at least once a week for highest level summoning.  I remember when you had a friggin spellbook in your face and it sucked bad.  That's all changed for the better for everyone not just the privileged that can play in large blocks of time consistently.
<br />

<br />
I'm off the soap box.  I veto the idea................<br />_________________<br />Sage Sarridon Soulcraver
<br />
Arch Convoker-Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
