				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sage Sarridon Soulcraver - Name one class that is as Uber as it gets the day it hits 65 and maxxes all AA.You can't. Gear for Melee translates to HP and STR. That equals tankability and DMG. All casters other than Mages , Mana makes a huge difference in their primary responsibilities. Healers can heal more, slower can slow, mezzers can mez, nukers can nuke. Mages are the most specialized class in the game. I personally don't think this is arguable. We cast pets foremost. We can nuke, but most of us are smart enough to have  a pet up before landing a nuke. Especially solo. What this thread has eluded to is the fact that Mana pool has very little effect on the survivability of the Mage class. Mana pool has a very definite effect on DPS/HealsPS of all other classes, when considering sustained output. 
<br />

<br />
I think the formulae above is excellent. I have a 39 SK that can hit harder than the numbers above. 
<br />

<br />
I have also heard alot about no drop uber pet toys. These would come as spells. That means at 65( Pet toys  would be a spell, hence you would have them by 65), if you were still doing tier 1, you would have a wickedly unfair pet(assuming the toys helped achieve a high end status).
<br />

<br />
Another idea I like, Pets leave corpses just like a PC. Then we could gear our pets up with some nice stuff. We would be dependent on gear for our pets. Then gear would affect scalability, like it does for other classes. We could buy some High HP gear for tanking a mob. We could buy some haste items for our rogue pet to hit faster. Just another thought.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
