<br />
I think the one thing you fail to understand is that YOU ARE NOT going to get a major pet damage boost (ie Sony won't do it), because in the pre-elementals game, WE DON'T NEED IT.  We need small improvements yes, but nothing huge.  Once melees aquire elemental weapons THEY WILL outdamage us!  When they get to time they REALLY outdamage us...rouges with Inny dagger/DoD with max worn atk can do DOUBLE our dps.  How can you not compare casters to melee??  Everyone else out there is doing it!  Whenever I try to get in Tipt groups I cannot because my guild's melees come close to my damage potential but offer much more utility (sneak/hide, pulling, etc) and we aren't even in time yet.  When the melees start outdamaging magicians we become USELESS.  The main and sole function of a raiding magician is damage...the other roles we play are extremely minor. 
<br />

<br />
You seem to just be envious of the high end characters who have worked extremely hard and had to play very well to get where they are.  I have admitted I am not one of these characters.  Look at my Magelo, I don't even have 5k mana unbuffed.  I have some nice gear, but some of it sucks.  I might understand your accusations if I was wearing a full suit of time+ gear and had a 7k+ mana pool, but I don't.  I just feel that this makes sense, and that it is the way that things should work to maintain class balanace.  Also, this would still mean upgrades for the vast majority of magicians, since most mages range from 4-5k mana, and the baseline in my proposal would start at 4k.  So you would see an improvement in your pet.  Tack on some mana augs from LDoN (something casual players can get!!) and it would improve even more!  This idea certainly does not leave the casual mage out in the cold, but also pays credit where credit is due.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370607" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tiiden Vandorgriffin</a>
