			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I dont even know why i spend those hours because i sure as hell didnt get the "ooooh" factor - not even after months framing and getting higher hp/mana - im still in same state.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Let me go over my last 5 pick-raid attempts at killing Grummus:
<br />

<br />
Attempt 1.  I died at 85% mana.
<br />
Attempt 2.  I died at full mana.
<br />
Attempt 3.  I died at 80% mana.
<br />
Attempt 4.  I died at 75% mana.
<br />
Attempt 5.  I died at 90% mana.
<br />

<br />
Tell me again your hps and resists don't improve your DPS over mine.  Keep on believing that, but you'll have to forgive me if I don't.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I wish we scaled like melees through the planes.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
So do the wizards, and necros, and clerics, and druids, and...
<br />
The fact remains, that you are significantly better than a non-raid equipped mage.  Is it enough?  I'm not at that stage of the game, so I don't know.  From the complaints of time+ geared mages I'd have to say it's not.  But I can say from personal experience that the non-uber mage also needs an upgrade to the pets.
<br />

<br />
However, I'm not that fond of Tiiden's suggestion for three reasons:  
<br />

<br />
First off, mana pool just isn't that important to the average player.  Let's face it, it's extremely rare in most group situations that you will ever go oom and wish you had a bigger mana pool.  Mana <span style="font-style: italic">regen</span> is the key.  If total mana pool determined my pet's melee abilities, then I would be forced to compromise between items that give me benefits such as more hps, flowing thought, and focus effects; and items that are just pure int/mana.  No other caster would have to make those compromises.
<br />

<br />
Secondly, corpse runs would be infinitely more difficult for mages compared to other casters.  We already have the penalty of not having any defensive spells (runes, roots, mez, snares, slows).  To tie our pet's abilities to our mana pool would seriously nerf the pet for a naked mage.  A naked mage (depending on race and starting sta allocation) would have roughly 1700 mana.  That would give us a 2000hp earth pet that hits for 34 damage on a corpse run...
<br />

<br />
And thirdly, you called me gimp.  Don't call me gimp if you are looking for support for your ideas.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597105" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Belthil Telperion</a>
<br />
65 Magician, Erollisi Marr</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
