			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not all mages should be the same or have the same abilities.  Xalmat will always have better gear than I will.  And he should.  He works harder and more consistantly than I do.  So be it.
<br />

<br />
I would rather they increase the frequency of drops of the pet focus items for those guys than to give everyone a blanket ability for all mages.  Maybe even increase the effect a bit more so that high end folks like Xal can dominate a mage like me.  Im all for that.
<br />

<br />
Im also for fixing up all mages some so their pets are more comparable with higher end game.  I am not a bazaar mage.  Im an LDON mage.  I have no idea where that puts me, but Im getting up there on AAs, FT and HP/Mana.  So where should I fit in?  In the middle I suspect and Im fine with that.  
<br />

<br />
Our pets need a logical boost that doesnt overpower us in general.  I like this idea.  But, my mana pool is getting pretty damn big.  When I go to GoD (not really interested just yet) and get some augs, it will jump even further.  The difference between someone like Xal and I would be less noticable as our mana pools reach larger numbers to the point where the difference between 1000 mana wont mean anything in pet damage.
<br />

<br />
But what you could do is make it a pet chant based on levels and/or spells of a series.  You cast it on the pet as a buff.  It continually drains your mana at 75 per tic (or something) until you cancel it.  But the effect on the pet would be profound, greatly increasing AC, HP, Damage and Attack (depending on spell level and/or AA level or maybe a combo of both).  Sort of like a burnout but much more.  
<br />

<br />
This will make the difference of mana and FT gear between Xalmat and myself much more profound.  He can chant his pet for a much longer time with his greater FT gear.  In addition, just mana pool alone, his +1000mana would allow him to outdamage me with his pet because I would have to cancel the chant and med up.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I like the idea overall.  But I also understand that folks on the higher end should have a gap between those that arnt going to put in the time.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
